"perftale  orb-ball.trace.json.gz

VERDICT
  60fps, 0 dropped frames — running close to budget
  bound    animation · 96% of main-thread frame time
  hotspot  sampleHeight  terrain/elevationField.ts:138 · 11ms self
  notes
    • React: 1023 component renders across 10 components (134ms, React DevTools timing).
      Most-rendered: ForwardRef(motion.div) ×381 — frequent re-renders are the usual
      culprit; check memoization / state placement. Timings include React DevTools
      recording overhead — capture without DevTools for true frame cost.
    • Dev build detected (React dev runtime) — record a production build for
      representative numbers.
    • Browser extensions were active during capture — engine/native time is inflated.
    • GC pressure: 5 scavenges (5.5/s) + 1 mark-compact cost 26ms of main-thread pauses.
      Hottest JS before scavenges (heuristic): _getGlobalBoundsRecursive — likely high
      allocation. Reduce per-frame allocations (pool/reuse objects); confirm with a heap
      allocation profile.
    • Forced synchronous layout: 60 forced reflows (12 layout + 48 style recalc, 6ms) — JS
      read layout geometry mid-frame, forcing the browser to flush layout inside script.
      That time is charged to script, so ~6ms of the 'animation' bound is synchronous
      layout, not animation work. Hottest JS in the run-up (heuristic): resetTransform —
      batch DOM reads before writes (read all geometry first, then write).

